  animalID: Bjorn
  animalName: Bjron
  species: 'Poison Dart Frog '
  scientificName: Dendrobates tinctorius
  status: 1
  biome: 1
  portrait: {fileID: 4723107735738678597, guid: 50522a9e83f69b343b694431706cb9a9, type: 3}
  journalArt: {fileID: 0}
  introDialogue: 'Oh good. Something big enough to actually DO something.

    

    

    I
    am Zara. I am also extremely poisonous so please do not touch me. I have said
    this to every animal in this forest and only about half of them listened.

    

    

    The
    loggers are getting closer. Three days ago they were a kilometre away. Today
    I can hear the saws.

    

    

    I cannot stop them. But before I ask
    for your help I need to know you actually understand what is being destroyed
    here. So. Quiz first. Then we talk.'
  questDialogue: 'The drilling crew. Three of them.

    That path is the only way
    to the seal colony. You are not afraid... interesting.


    I will wait here.'
  completionDialogue: 'I have lived my entire life in a ten metre radius.

    This
    forest is not a resource. It is my entire world.

    

    Thank you for understanding
    that.

    

    Here. For my new friend.'
  journalEntry: "Journal Entry\r\nPoison Dart Frog | Dendrobates tinctorius\r\nStatus:
    Endangered \u2014 population declining\r\n\r\nPoison dart frogs get their toxicity
    entirely from\r\ntheir diet of specific rainforest insects. Remove them from
    their habitat and they lose their poison within one generation. They are a perfect
    example of how deeply connected every species is to its ecosystem.\r\n\r\nThey
    are also indicator species \u2014 one of the first\r\nanimals to disappear when
    a rainforest is degraded. If dart frogs are gone, the forest is already dying.\r\n\r\nThey
    are heavily targeted by the illegal exotic pet\r\ntrade. A single frog can sell
    for hundreds of dollars.\r\n\r\nWhat you can do: Never buy exotic amphibians
    as pets.\r\n\r\nSupport Rainforest Trust at rainforesttrust.org"
  conservationFact: 'Polar bear fur is actually transparent, not white. It scatters
    light the same way snow does. '
  doofNote: 'I once tried making the Arctic colder with a Cryo-Inator. It worked
    locally for about 45 minutes. Climate is complicated. The real solution is emissions
    reduction, not Inatoring.  Fun fact: Bjorn means bear in Norse.'
  questType: 0
  linkedQuiz: {fileID: 0}
  rewardItemID: WindmillBoots
